PLACEHOLDER. Replace with the maintainer's PGP public key in armored
ASCII form before tagging v0.2 or any release that wants the email
channel in SECURITY.md to be operative.

Generate with:

    gpg --quick-generate-key "Gemma.Witness security <security@aftermath.tech>" rsa4096 cert,sign,encrypt 2y
    gpg --armor --export security@aftermath.tech > docs/security-pgp-key.asc

Publish the same fingerprint in three places that stay in lockstep:

  1. This file (the key itself).
  2. SECURITY.md "Reporting a vulnerability" section (the fingerprint
     hash, abbreviated to the last 16 hex chars for readability).
  3. The maintainer's keybase / keys.openpgp.org listing for the same
     email, so cross-checking the fingerprint out-of-band is possible.

Rotate the key on a planned schedule (annually) and on any suspected
compromise. Sign the new key with the old one and publish the signed
transition statement under `docs/security-key-transitions/`.

Until this placeholder is replaced, the email channel in SECURITY.md
should be treated as "request the key first via GitHub private vuln
reports, then encrypt with the key the maintainer sends back."
